    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="67"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d67">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Moscow Embassy Files—500 Berlin Conference</note>
                <head>No. 67 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the First Secretary of Embassy in the Soviet
                        Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PEJ1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-15">June 15,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum of Conversation</hi>
                </p>
                <table>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Present:</cell>
                        <cell> The Ambassador</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_PEJ1">Page</persName>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_V2">Vyshinski</persName>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_P1">Postoev</persName>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
                <p>The Ambassador stated that he wished to bring up the subject of the preparation
                    for the forthcoming Berlin meeting. <persName corresp="#p_DMGJR1">General
                        Deane</persName> had received instructions from <persName
                        corresp="#p_EGADD1">General Eisenhower</persName> to obtain permission for
                    an advance group to proceed to Berlin on June 17 to make preliminary
                    arrangements. The Ambassador said that he desired to leave with Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_V2">Vyshinski</persName> a copy of <persName corresp="#p_DMGJR1"
                        >General Deane</persName>’s letter<note n="1" xml:id="d67fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> on the subject and to state that he was always prepared to
                    discuss the matter with Mr. <persName corresp="#p_V2">Vyshinski</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PEJ1">E[<hi rend="smallcaps">dward</hi>] P[<hi
                                rend="smallcaps">age</hi>, Jr.]</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
